  "rule_text": "The Brand Accent Shape (core container device) table is a closed, brand-approved set; every row binds its listed values exactly as specified. Do not invent or alter rows.\n\n| item | value |\n|---|---|\n| Approved radius pairs (print) | **1.25\" & 0.0625\"** (large containers/photos), **0.5\" & 0.0625\"** (banners), **0.4375\" & 0.0625\"** (small callout boxes). |\n| [GENERAL] Email px conversions (at 96dpi) | ** large: 120px & 6px; banner: 48px & 6px; callout: 42px & 6px. Apply the large radius to one diagonal pair (e.g., top-left + bottom-right), the 6px radius to the other pair. Be consistent within an email: same diagonal orientation across all sections (default: large radius top-left & bottom-right). |\n| Exception | charts and tables use uniform rounded corners on all four corners** (not the asymmetric accent shape). [GENERAL: 12px uniform radius.] |",
  "intent": "Bind the Brand Accent Shape (core container device) table values verbatim.",
  "source": "design_bible",
  "doc_ref": "design_pattern_rules[3]",
  "group_id": "grp_lisraya_design_pattern_rules_03",
  "status": "active",
  "version": 1,
  "summary": "Brand Accent Shape radius pairs (print) fixed: 1.25\"/0.0625\" large, 0.5\"/0.0625\" banners, 0.4375\"/0.0625\" callouts; email px: large=120/6, banner=48/6, callout=42/6 with consistent diagonal orientation; charts/tables uniform 12px radius."
